jenkins -- ci/cd

Architecture -- master/agent 
jenkins master -- actuall console   / jenkins agent -- created by master when running a pipeline

hh -->
jenkins master is on ec2
and jenkins agent is on dev cluster

master -- only one instace, also it can be a docker container, kubernetes pod, or a sepereate ec2 server
agents -- it can be , a docker container, kubernetes pod, or a sepereate ec2 server  -- can be multiple


1 gitrepo -- jenkinsfile(actuall pipeline) --> jenkins console pipeline configure


authentication methods:
1. jenkins database -- stored on the jenkins master
2. saml2.0 -- 3rd party identity provider -- okta,keycloak,microsoft saml -- most used -- hh
3. ldap -- linux/ldap based authentication

authorization:
1. matrix based -- works best with saml


jenkins -- master - seperate server/ agent -- seperate or same server
github actions -- master is managed by github -- agents are managed my customer

forge -- sepereate server

dev build --> repo push --> action --> paste in the ngixn dir
